pr_review_comment_body:
The If macro encapsulates the 1 in a Value object and so this behaves correctly.

From macros.py:
```python
def If(predicate, subcon, elsevalue = None):
    return IfThenElse(subcon.name,
        predicate,
        subcon,
        Value("elsevalue", lambda ctx: elsevalue)
    )
```

Not especially, although setting an environment variable is a bit risky (since it may affect an environment variable in use). Perhaps something along the lines of (leaving out the redirection for brevity):

```sh
{ cd '/some/path' && echo 0; } || { echo $?; exit 1; }
# Other commands
```

It might be nicer to include the command when echoing the result from `cd` and `which` so that the output is slightly more readable and easier to debug (or when the outputs are misaligned, as happens sometimes when the shell produces extra unexpected output) e.g.

```sh
{ cd '/some/path' && echo cd 0; } || { echo cd $?; exit 1; }
{ { command -v cmd || which cmd; } && echo which 0; } || { echo which $?; exit 1; }
```

